thanks for the contribution, great to see a test :-) however I removed the mods to afterPropertiesSet and the test still works!
One other thought  - the call to startManagementContext needs to be gated with shouldAutostart,
there are use cases where a spring context creates the broker bean for later start up.: 

if (shouldAutostart() && isUseJmx() && !getManagementContext().isStarted()) {
      startManagementContext();
}

@gtully Somehow I removed the key statement from the test when I was cleaning up:

``` java
  broker.setSchedulerSupport(true); 
```

It is actually blocking during jobScheduler.start(), whilst the scheduler is trying to get hold of shared file lock.

SharedFileLocker.doStart() line 52:

``` java
  while ((!isStopped()) && (!isStopping())) {
```

I'll add back in this statement and make the suggested change.  I wonder though, whether I've added the fix in the correct place?
